# Trivy IMAGE-CVE ignore list — P1 W6-T5.
#
# Scope: the `docker` job's image scans (netops-backend:ci / netops-frontend:ci)
# ONLY. This is SEPARATE from deploy/kubernetes/.trivyignore (which suppresses
# IaC-misconfig findings for the infra job's `trivy config` scan, a different
# finding type). Keeping them apart prevents a misconfig suppression from ever
# silencing a real CVE and vice-versa.
#
# Gate posture (NOT lowered): the image scan fails on CRITICAL **and** HIGH
# (severity: CRITICAL,HIGH) with ignore-unfixed (un-patchable base-OS CVEs with
# no upstream fix are out of our control — see
# docs/security/2026-06-14-trivy-baseimage-cves.md). A finding is suppressed ONLY
# by adding it BELOW with a justification + a re-review/expiry date. An entry
# without both is a review defect. This file is currently EMPTY of accepted
# findings: the raise to CRITICAL,HIGH is clean on the current images, so nothing
# is suppressed. Never add a blanket/severity-wide ignore — only specific CVE IDs.
#
# Format (one per accepted finding):
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # <why accepted> — re-review <YYYY-MM-DD>
#
# --- accepted findings (none) ---
